sentences.english: A big investor is very displeased.
sentences.chinese: 一位大投資者則非常不滿。

sentences.english: Farmers are revolting over a new sliding-scale increase in export taxes.
sentences.chinese: 農場主對新出臺的出口稅率浮動上調政策非常不滿。

sentences.english: The rebellion was started by some malcontents who had been dissatisfied with the policy.
sentences.chinese: 造反源於那些對於政策不滿的人。

sentences.english: Temporary foreigners' residence permits shall be issued to those residing in China for less than a year.
sentences.chinese: 外國人臨時居留證，發給在中國居留不滿一年的人員。

sentences.english: It used to be that much of this discontent boiled under the surface.
sentences.chinese: 在過去，許多不滿情緒在社會表層下沸騰。

sentences.english: The unsatisfied workers are rioting in the streets.
sentences.chinese: 心懷不滿的工人們在大街上鬧事。

sentences.english: They contributed tactlessly to a general discontent.
sentences.chinese: 他們行爲的不策略造成了普遍的不滿。

sentences.english: Pairs of Private Vocational Colleges dissatisfied with lack of self-affirmation, strong inferiority complex.
sentences.chinese: 對民辦高職院校感到不滿，自我肯定不足，自卑感強。

sentences.english: The thermometer of success is merely the jealousy of the malcontents.
sentences.chinese: 不滿者的嫉妒，是成功的溫度計。

sentences.english: The only complaints in recent years have been that the roosters are too loud.
sentences.chinese: 近年來對他們唯一的不滿就是啦啦隊的聲音太大了。

sentences.english: However, many mooncake buyers expressed their dismay at the overly-elaborated boxes.
sentences.chinese: 然而許多月餅買家對過分精美的盒子表示了不滿。

sentences.english: Thepeople cried out againsttheunjust imprisonment of the honest doctor.
sentences.chinese: 人們對不公正地囚禁那位正直的醫生表示強烈不滿。

sentences.english: Larry Goodson says that left a lot of residual bad feeling towards the U.S. in Pakistan.
sentences.chinese: 拉里古德森說，這使巴基斯坦對美國留下了很多不滿。

sentences.english: On the field anomaly dissatisfaction with the determined to prove his ability.
sentences.chinese: 上田異常不滿地下決心要證明自己的能力。

sentences.english: The teachers picketed outside of the school building to express their frustration over low wages.
sentences.chinese: 教師們在校舍外示威，對低工資表示不滿。

sentences.english: There are two reasons philanthropy gets people riled up in China.
sentences.chinese: 慈善在中國引發公衆不滿原因有二。

definition: to fight against/to oppose/to be opposed to/opposition
to criticize/to find fault with/to denounce
for this reason/with regards to this/in this respect/in order to do this/to this end
to call into question/to question (truth or validity)
regarding/as far as sth is concerned/with regards to
to approve of/to endorse/to acknowledge/to recognize/to identify oneself with
